<br>
Then one day I threw it at an orc pawn. And it went flying and whapped him upside the head. Needless to say, I got a big kick out of that and kept it up.<br>
<br>
It'd only do about as much damage as anything else you threw, but eh, it was just fun.<br>
<br>
Now I can't do that anymore.<br>
<br>
Which is odd, because, well they still sell THROWING AXES in cities like FP and Qeynos and Katta. And it isn't really much of a stretch to conceive of someone throwing a hammer or a club or any other blunt object at a monster.<br>
<br>
Anyways, I agree with Varanuss. VI may not fix bards. They may not fix Paladin LoH. They may not fix BL warder attacks. BUT THIS ... this is the last straw. Expect an emergency Splintering Club BUG FIX patch soon. <br>
<br>
:-)<br>
